# Git commit messages (including "Generate Commit Message" in Source Control)

Generated git commit messages MUST be short. One line only unless breaking change or security.

- Format: `type(scope): imperative summary` (scope optional)
- Types: feat, fix, refactor, perf, docs, test, chore, build, ci, style, revert
- Subject MAX 50 characters (hard cap 72). Imperative mood. No trailing period.
- NO commit body. NO multi-sentence subject. Do not list files or describe "improvements".
- Never start with "This commit", "Update", "Enhance", or restate the whole diff.

Examples:
- `fix(setup): align toolbar divider`
- `refactor(crew): compact upcoming grid`

Bad (never output this style):
- `Refactor CSS styles for setup toolbar components to improve layout and responsiveness...`
